               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 9 works (a-i)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous Persian and Arabic works on Sufism, lexicography, and vocabulary, comprised of various tractates assembled from different sources. Volume not dated; individual items range in date between the late seventeenth to early nineteenth centuries. Variable scribal naskh, nastaʿlīq, and shikastah āmīz hands. Only the boards of a later leather binding survive. Stamped foliation. Folios detached and unbound; cropped, wormhole damage, later repairs. Condition fragile. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1164-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="98r">ff. 1v-98r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī treatise emphasising divine unity and agency, which also critiques Muslims with differing opinions, by Muḥammad Farrukh ibn Shaykh Muḥammad Saʿīd al-Naqshbandī al-Aḥmadī. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Refer to IOL microfilm 118. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21686">Kashf al-ghiṭāʾ ʿan az̲hān al-aghbiyāʾ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21686">كشف الغطاء عن اذهان الاغبياء</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7350"> Muḥammad Farrukh ibn Shaykh Muḥammad Saʿīd al-Naqshbandī al-Aḥmadī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7350">محمّد فرّخ ابن محمّد سعيد النّقشبندى الاحمدى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1164-item2">
                     <locus from="101v" to="147r">ff. 101v-147r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7655">Nūr</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7655">نور</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21687">Anīs al-ghurabāʾ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21687">انيس الغرباء</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Treatise on Sufism by an author identifying himself as Nūr, but entitled in the superscription as Quṭb-i ʿĀlam. 
</p>
                        <p>The work was intended to compliment the treatise <title>Muʾnis al-fuqarāʾ</title> by a student of ʿAlāʾ al-Dīn ʿUmar Lāhawrī, which dates to the early fifteenth century. Arberry has argued this is the basis for fixing the present author’s period of work to the period immediately following the composition of the Muʾnis al-fuqarāʾ. 

                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 147r): completed at noon on Thursday, 6 Muḥarram in RY 39 (? ruler not indicated). 
</p>
                        <p>Refer to IOL microfilm 119. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1164-item3">
                     <locus from="149v" to="164r">ff. 149v-164r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī treatise on the fundamental principles of faith in God by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Among the authorities cited in the work is the famous muḥaddis̲, ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq al-Sayfī al-Dihlavī, indicating the work dates from the seventeenth century or later. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21688">al-Ḥadd al-fāṣil bayna sadīd al-iʿtiqād va bayna al-zindiqat va al-ilḥād</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21688">الحدّ الفاصل بين سديد الاعتقاد و بين الزّندقة و الالحاد</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1164-item4">
                     <locus from="165v" to="195v">ff. 165v-195v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Fragment of a Persian translation from the Arabic Ṣūfī treatise on the principles of Islām by the proponent of Shuhūdī thought, ʿAlāʾ al-Dawlah Abū al-Makārim Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad ibn Aḥmad al-Simnānī (d. 736/1336). 
</p>
                        <p>The original version was completed on Tuesday, 13 Muḥarram 721/20 February 1321 at the Masjid of Ṣūfī'ābād, but the present Persian edition was completed 1 Jumādá I 722/26 May 1322, being sponsored by the author’s son, Abū al-Barakāt Taqī al-Dīn ʿAlī Simnānī. 
</p>
                        <p>The work consists of six bāb. 
</p>
                        <p>The text ends abruptly, without appropriate conclusion. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21689">al-ʿUrvat li-al-ahl al-khalvat va al-jalvah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21689">العروة لاهل الخلوة و الجلوة</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="person_17351669" type="supplied" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">ʿAlāʾ al-Dawlah Abū al-Makārim Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad ibn Aḥmad al-Simnānī (d. 736/1336)</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_17351669">علاء الدّوله ابو المكارم احمد السّمنانى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1164-item5">
                     <locus from="197v" to="272v">ff. 197v-272v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. </p>
                        <p>Arabic Ṣūfī treatise on the fundamentals of religious beliefs and practice by Muḥammad Bayg ibn Yār Muḥammad ibn Khvājah Muḥammad, who completed the work in Rajab 1084/October 1673. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Multiple naskh hands throughout, with an impressively bold basmalah design at the beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Later annotations in margins. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21690">Fāʾiz̤ al-munībīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21690">فائض المنيبين</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7346">Muḥammad Bayg ibn Yār Muḥammad, fl. 1673</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f7346">محمّد بيگ ابن يار محمّد</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1164-item6">
                     <locus from="275v" to="316v">ff. 275v-316v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item f. </p>
                        <p>Arabic treatise entitled Navādir al-lughah on vocabulary, by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Pale green and orange tinted papers. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21691">Navādir al-lughah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21691">نوادر اللّغة</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="7" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1164-item7">
                     <locus from="317r" to="319v">ff. 317r-319v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item g. </p>
                        <p>Brief, untitled Arabic lexicographic treatise on antonyms or words capable of baring meanings opposite to their primary definition, by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Transcribed obliquely in shikastah āmīz, with annotations by the same scribe in margins (cropped). 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="8" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1164-item8">
                     <locus from="320r" to="320r">ff. 320r-320r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item h. </p>
                        <p>Unidentified Arabic text. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="9" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1164-item9">
                     <locus from="320v" to="328v">ff. 320v-328v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item i. </p>
                        <p>Untitled Arabic lexicographic treatise on Persian vocabulary absorbed into courtly Arabic by the author Muḥammad ibn Badr al-Dīn al-Munshīʾ. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7363" type="supplied">Muḥammad ibn Badr al-Dīn al-Munshīʾ</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7363" type="supplied">محمّد ابن بدر الدّين المنشىٴ</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
